00053 // Get a single mesh or die trying
00054 static FC_ReturnCode getMeshByNameOrDie(FC_Dataset ds, char *mesh_name, FC_Mesh *m){
00055 
00056   FC_ReturnCode rc;
00057   FC_Mesh *meshes;
00058   int numMeshes;
00059 
00060   rc = fc_getMeshByName(ds, mesh_name, &numMeshes, &meshes);
00061   fc_exitIfError(rc);
00062   
00063   if(numMeshes!=1)
00064     emsg("Found %d meshes named %s", numMeshes, mesh_name);
00065 
00066   *m = meshes[0];
00067   FREE(meshes);
00068   return FC_SUCCESS;
00069 
00070 }

00072 void dumpHelp(){
00073   int i, rc;
00074   char *name, *sname, *description;
00075   int id;
00076   printf("Whittle Tree: a tool for reducing a spanning tree to a smaller representation\n"
00077       "  This tool takes an input file that holds a spanning tree and then whittles\n"
00078          "  the structure to a smaller form in order to provide a more convenient way\n"
00079          "  to examine and compare one or more meshes.\n"
00080       "\n"
00081       "Usage: whittle_tree [options] <algorithm>\n"
00082       "  [-i input file  ]                input file (default=result_tree.e)\n"
00083       "  [-o output file ]                output file (default=result_tree_whittled.e)\n" 
00084       "  [-m mesh_name[step]]             can be appended with displacement step, like block_1[2])\n"
00085       "  [-d displacement_variable_name ] (does combinding on _x,_y,_z and defaults to 'displacement')\n"
00086       "  [-p 0-99 ]                       desired percentage of nodes to survive\n"           
00087       "   -v                              display warning messages\n"
00088       "   -V                              display log messages\n"
00089       "   -S                              Silent operation: don't print info\n"
00090          "   -h                              this help screen\n"
00091       "   -w algorithm                    select whittle algorithm\n");
00092 
00093   for(i=0; (rc=getNextWhittleAlgorithmDescription(i,&name, &sname, &id, &description)); i++){
00094     printf("        %s : %23s - %s\n", sname, name, description);
00095   }
00096 
00097   exit(0);
00098 }

00103 int main(int argc, char **argv){
00104 
00105   FC_ReturnCode rc;
00106   FC_VerbosityLevel verbose_level = FC_WARNING_MESSAGES;
00107   FC_Dataset ds;
00108   FC_Mesh m;
00109   int ich;
00110   int percent = 75;
00111   spanning_tree_t *tree1, *tree2;
00112 
00113   char *file_name_i = "result_tree.e";
00114   char *file_name_o = "result_tree_whittled.e";
00115   char *mesh_name   = "skel_mesh";
00116   char *disp_name   = "displacement";
00117   int whittle_type=0;
00118 
00119   double remaining_fraction;
00120 
00121 
00122   _skeleton_dbg=1; //Default to printing info
00123 
00124 
00125   if(argc==1) dumpHelp();
00126   
00127   while( (ich = getopt(argc, argv, "o:i:m:d:p:w:SvVhH")) != EOF){
00128     switch(ich){
00129     case 'i':  file_name_i   = strdup(optarg); break;
00130     case 'o':  file_name_o   = strdup(optarg); break;
00131     case 'm':  mesh_name     = strdup(optarg); break;
00132     case 'd':  disp_name     = strdup(optarg); break;
00133     case 'p':  percent       = atoi(optarg);   break;
00134     case 'w':  whittle_type  = convertStringToWhittleAlg(optarg); break;
00135 
00136     case 'S':  _skeleton_dbg = 0;                   break;
00137     case 'v':  verbose_level = FC_WARNING_MESSAGES; break;
00138     case 'V':  verbose_level = FC_LOG_MESSAGES;     break;
00139     case 'h':
00140     case 'H':
00141     default:
00142       dumpHelp(); break;
00143     }
00144   }
00145 
00146   if(optind<argc)
00147     file_name_i = strdup(argv[optind++]);
00148 
00149 
00150   //Pass back info to user
00151   info("whittle_tree is running with args\n"
00152        "\tInput File   = '%s'\n"
00153        "\tOutput File  = '%s'\n"
00154        "\tMesh Name    = '%s'\n"
00155        "\tDisplacement = '%s'\n"
00156        "\tAlgorithm    = '%s'\n"
00157        "\tPercent      =  %d%%'",
00158        file_name_i,
00159        file_name_o,
00160        mesh_name,
00161        disp_name,
00162        getWhittleAlgorithmName(whittle_type),
00163        percent);  
00164 
00165 
00166   //Setup
00167   rc = fc_setLibraryVerbosity(verbose_level);           fc_exitIfError(rc);
00168   rc = fc_initLibrary();                                fc_exitIfError(rc);
00169 
00170   //Load the first mesh
00171   rc = fc_loadDataset(file_name_i, &ds);                fc_exitIfError(rc);
00172   rc = getMeshByNameOrDie(ds, mesh_name, &m);           fc_exitIfError(rc); 
00173 
00174   //Get the mesh
00175   fc_unpackSkeletonFromMesh(m, &tree1);         
00176 
00177   //Send off to the whittle routine
00178   remaining_fraction = ((double)percent)/100.0;
00179   rc = whittleSkeleton(tree1, whittle_type, 
00180                  remaining_fraction, &tree2);     fc_exitIfError(rc); 
00181 
00182 
00183 
00184 
00185   //Save it out
00186   rc = fc_saveSkeleton(*tree2, disp_name, file_name_o); fc_exitIfError(rc);
00187 
00188   printf("Done");
00189   return 0;
00190 }
